Building the Sitar documentation
================================

The docs are built with mkdocs. The build needs Python 3 and a few packages,
all listed in `requirements.txt`.

Commands below use two working directories:
  - Run pip commands from this `docs/` directory.
  - Run `mkdocs` commands from the repo root (where `mkdocs.yml` lives).


One-time setup
--------------

From the repo root:

    python3 -m venv .venv

Activate the virtualenv (do this once per shell session):

    source .venv/bin/activate

Install the dependencies. This also pulls in the custom Pygments lexer used
for Sitar syntax highlighting (the `-e ../sitar_pygments_lexer` line inside
`requirements.txt`):

    cd docs
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    cd ..


Build the static site
---------------------

With the venv active, from the repo root:

    mkdocs build

The output goes to `generated_site/`.


Preview locally
---------------

With the venv active, from the repo root:

    mkdocs serve

Then open the printed localhost URL in a browser. Pages rebuild live as you
edit `.md` files.


Done for the day
----------------

    deactivate
